      "title": "[DC] sirtealot@🔸有問必答┊official-q-a: As of now, D-Effect Zone (aka DTide) happens to be the one game mode that the ma",
      "summary": "As of now, D-Effect Zone (aka DTide) happens to be the one game mode that the majority of endgame players (at least in the EN community) agrees to be the most engaging, as it provides a good amount of challenge while also giving a reason to utilize characters that are otherwise left unused. \n\nHowever, two weeks often ends up being a bit too much time for a reasonably developed account, resulting in the second week of the rotation feeling rather dry in terms of things to do. \nI do also recognize that this is not the case for players with less developed accounts, who would be put under too much stress with a weekly rotation cycle. \nTherefore, I humbly suggest a few potentially possible solutions: \n- A second set of DTide waves available after clearing the first one, having the same rotation cycle and perhaps using the enemy lineups from past DTides, allowing the players to try the previous challenges with a different realm ring. The rewards for clearing it could be minimal.\n- Alternatively, the second set of waves could mirror the current ones, but add a number of restrictions for realms/awakeners that can be used to clear each wave. \n- As another suggestion, it could be the same set of waves, but without the realm ring, providing an opportunity to try out the teams without the benefits of dimensional image relics. \n\nUltimately, the request just comes down to having more DTide-adjacent things to do, that would be quite nice, I think  \nEither way, thank you to whoever ends up reading through this, please leave your thoughts, suggestions and concerns below!!",
      "url": "https://discord.com/channels/1131791637933199470/1526407849796829204/1526407849796829204",
